# Orthogonal Slice Extraction Usage Guide

The neuroimjs library now provides functionality to extract orthogonal slices (axial, sagittal, and coronal) from 3D neuroimaging volumes at specified world-space coordinates, matching the Python pyneuroim library's capabilities.

## API Overview

### Main Functions

#### `extractOrthogonalSlices(vol, worldPoint, sliceTypes?)`
Extract one or more orthogonal slices from a volume at a given world-space point.

```typescript
import { extractOrthogonalSlices } from 'neuroimjs';

// Extract all three orthogonal slices at world point (10, 20, 30)
